[[include :scp-wiki:info:end]]

+ Usage

This is a Sigma-9 theme based on the current [http://wanderers-library.wikidot.com Wanderer's Library] CSS Theme. For the BHL version of this theme, [[[theme:dustjacket|see here]]]. For a theme based on the original Wanderer's Library CSS theme, [[[theme:wanderers|see here]]].

This theme is intended to be applied to the articles related to the Wanderers' Library, such as the [[[goi-formats#sh|Serpent's Hand formats]]].

To import this theme to your page, put the following anywhere inside it:

> @@[[include :scp-wiki:theme:dustjacket-sigma]]@@

You can view any page's Backlinks by clicking "+ Options" at the bottom of the page, then "Backlinks".

+ Examples

[[include component:image-block name= https://wanderers-library.wdfiles.com/local--files/component%3Atheme/wandererslibary_logobg.png|caption=Logo for The Wanderers' Library|width=200px]]

A horizontal rule can be created with 4 hyphens "@@----@@" and extends across the whole page if it's not placed inside anything (eg a blockquote). The lines separating sections of this document are horizontal rules.

----

An alternative horizontal rule is available as well if the "@@----@@" is enclosed in a "fancyhr" class div, like so:
> @@[[div_ class="fancyhr"]]@@
> @@----@@
> @@[[/div]]@@

Resulting in this:

[[div_ class="fancyhr"]]
----
[[/div]]

[[div_ class="fancyborder"]]
There is also a special border that can be enabled by adding the "fancyborder" class to any element. For instance, this is the code to this block:
[[div_ class="code"]]
@@[[div_ class="fancyborder"]]@@
@@content goes here@@
@@[[/div]]@@
[[/div]]
[[/div]]

Footnotes gain a "(" or "," in front of them.[[footnote]]This allows you to put footnotes next to each other in more pleasing fashion.[[/footnote]][[footnote]]Some browsers may not support this feature optimally.[[/footnote]]

[[footnoteblock]]

Titles can be created by putting between one and six plus "+" at the start of the line

[[collapsible show="+ Titles" hide="- Titles"]]
+ First Title

++ Second Title

+++ Third Title

++++ Fourth Title

+++++ Fifth Title

++++++ Sixth Title
[[/collapsible]]

